-- U.S. RESEARCH ROUNDUP-Broadcom, Verizon, McDonald's  
-- 
-- Wed Jul 23, 2014 03:15AM EDT
-- None



July 23 (Reuters) - Wall Street securities analysts revised their ratings and price targets on several U.S.-listed companies, including Verizon Communications and Broadcom Corp, on Wednesday.

HIGHLIGHTS * Broadcom Corp <BRCM.O>: Oppenheimer raises price target to $50 from $45; rating outperform * Verizon Communications <VZ.N> : JP Morgan, Canaccord Genuity raise target On the stock  * Xilinx <XLNX.O>: Jefferies, Credit Suisse cut price target on stock   Following is a summary of research actions on U.S. companies reported by Reuters on Wednesday. Stock entries are in alphabetical order.* Allegheny Technologies <ATI.N> : Keybanc cuts price target to $51 from $53; rating buy * Broadcom Corp <BRCM.O>: Oppenheimer raises price target to $50 from $45; rating outperform * Cathay General Bancorp <CATY.O> : BMO raises price target to $29; rating outperform  * Diamondback Energy <FANG.O> : Sterne Agee raises target to $118 from $116; rating buy * Diamondback Energy <FANG.O>:Sterne Agee raises price target to $118 from $116; rating buy  * Exact Sciences <EXAS.O>: Canaccord Genuity raises target to $19 from $18 ; rating buy * Juniper Networks <JNPR.N> : Piper Jaffray cuts target to $26 from $28; rating neutral * Lockheed Martin <LMT.N> : JP Morgan raises price target to $155 from $144; rating neutral * McDonald's <MCD.N> : Buckingham Research cuts price target to $98; rating neutral  * Robert Half <RHI.N>: Deutsche Bank raises price target to $55 from $48; rating buy * State Street <STT.N> : Jefferies cuts price target to $76 from $78; rating buy * Verizon Communications <VZ.N> : JP Morgan raises target to $59 from $58; rating overweight * Verizon Communications <VZ.N>: Canaccord Genuity raises target to $56 from $55; rating buy * Xilinx <XLNX.O>: Jefferies cuts price target to $48 from $53; rating hold